    <p><strong>About 'This Is Our Stop'</strong></p>
    <p>A conversation space that connects transit riders through their bus stops. Inspired by <a href="http://www.countablyinfinite.ca/">Karen Quinn Fung</a>'s urban planning research, we hope to make city life more friendly and our transit infrastructure even better.<p>

    <p><b>This Is Our Stop</b> <em>is not affiliated with Translink. Route and arrival data used in this service is provided by permission of TransLink. TransLink assumes no responsibility for the accuracy or currency of the Data used in this service.</em></p>

    <p><em>This Is Our Stop</em> is an open-source project by <a href="http://denimandsteel.com">Denim &amp; Steel Interactive</a> and <a href="http://sam.dalmonte.ca/">Sam Dal Monte</a>. Grab the code at <a href="https://github.com/denimandsteel/thisisourstop">the Github page</a>.

	<p>Send questions and comments by email to <a href="mailto:hello@denimandsteel.com">hello@denimandsteel.com</a> or follow <a href="http://twitter.com/thisisourstop>"@thisisourstop on Twitter</a>.</p>
